Subject: [PATCH] spi: bcm63xx: Fix module autoloading
References: bsc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 6.11.3
Git-commit: 909f34f2462a99bf876f64c5c61c653213e32fce

commit 909f34f2462a99bf876f64c5c61c653213e32fce upstream.

Add MODULE_DEVICE_TABLE(), so modules could be properly autoloaded
based on the alias from platform_device_id table.

Fixes: 44d8fb30941d ("spi/bcm63xx: move register definitions into the driver")
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Jinjie Ruan <ruanjinjie@huawei.com>
Reviewed-by: Jonas Gorski <jonas.gorski@gmail.com>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20240819123349.4020472-2-ruanjinjie@huawei.com
Signed-off-by: Mark Brown <broonie@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
---
 drivers/spi/spi-bcm63xx.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/spi/spi-bcm63xx.c b/drivers/spi/spi-bcm63xx.c
index 2fb8d4e55c77..650ab4b2e688 100644
--- a/drivers/spi/spi-bcm63xx.c
+++ b/drivers/spi/spi-bcm63xx.c
@@ -466,6 +466,7 @@ static const struct platform_device_id bcm63xx_spi_dev_match[] = {
 	{
 	},
 };
+MODULE_DEVICE_TABLE(platform, bcm63xx_spi_dev_match);
 
 static const struct of_device_id bcm63xx_spi_of_match[] = {
 	{ .compatible = "brcm,bcm6348-spi", .data = &bcm6348_spi_reg_offsets },
